headline: S&P Global Mobility: Solid finish to close out 2024 US auto sales
summary: December U.S. auto sales are estimated to hit 1.45 million units, translating to an estimated sales pace of 16.5 million units (seasonally adjusted annual rate: SAAR), according to S&P Global Mobility. This would match the month prior reading and result in a fourth quarter selling rate average of 16.4 million units, a step up from the 15.6 million units averaged over the previous three quarters of the year, and the highest quarterly average for this metric since Q2 2021.
